{"id": "0e48b7ab432654444be0cd2df7cde8b453ef519ff468d61a671ed646143c4b52", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:0", "text": "This node is meant to work in conjunction with PxrProjectionLayer but can be used as a general projection manifold. This manifold supports camera, spherical and cylindrical mapping. It encapsulates 2D parameterization for pattern generators and allows transformations and selection of arbitrary variables bound to primitives."}
{"id": "54be5f95d16052f1446591cbd08c5598a2be27aa36faf18e955e8b2dfb1fec8a", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:2", "text": "Projection"}
{"id": "545eb19a40fbf9dae20f4154891da944404106055b33dc0b48fd457696508c47", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:3", "text": "Select a projection:"}
{"id": "a3ca2004998580248cff727b1e0bee5510c52244646f31f69348fc7bd105a244", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:4", "text": "0: Camera"}
{"id": "72fa3ca55aea0df5e34908e9cd141f1c693a877efefcdd01f76e60315a3bcfe0", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:5", "text": "1: Spherical"}
{"id": "88b0d83d1daac1031c8a598ec8b8474f7142fac08ec750a32a1b5c2dfa0fb45b", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:6", "text": "2: Cylindrical"}
{"id": "155730bc4c5646597f9f6504fbb8c46d81422c4c99c45ecfc346e6487b79611f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:7", "text": "3: Planar"}
{"id": "b514ebf73921fea11670ca9640e96c27bc4e980867839d368eca5bd872bd174f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:8", "text": "Coordinate System"}
{"id": "3badf7f9ecddeb948bae2ee1d7dd20ffd13ae3f30722c03b2e4ad6798c94fe98", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:9", "text": "Name of coordinate system transform (e.g. place3dTexture node in Maya or the camera)."}
{"id": "08b041935798fbf6fd6ff51099ffedb140a475889986d14f5559ff8e7fc571dd", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:10", "text": "You"}
{"id": "4137b01e139589b7a1d3b3fc4da031d8ce5bb415808734e970c3a58ea0e98f0f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:11", "text": "must"}
{"id": "78111a5ad0b9bcb917fd148749e3cdc29e4c7a2b18abbed869a9261ea6ca5a43", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:12", "text": "set a coordinate system. This field can not be left empty."}
{"id": "c0ebf7c7d90c298edf6d64ba257a6fd2bb1a66560c4179632e3df357741a3967", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:14", "text": "Selects the positions you are going to project on."}
{"id": "809b1486d827226ec05018b987a27adfb25dc57c925107ac039adbfbf5d5c431", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:15", "text": "0: P - N"}
{"id": "7d6319fc6a2a8bba0c16b92c5e1e93ed14e907217bef4ad32f14fc96c884a6fd", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:16", "text": "P is the current position and N the current normal"}
{"id": "fa8790103a974044e297d7de8ed9ab55334a325301992b80c7933f46d26c617b", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:17", "text": "1: Pref - Nref"}
{"id": "d5f61ecbb8868ed294c37b65cef4746953af017d61622fad31916044d402374f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:18", "text": "Use this if your object if deforming and you want the projected texture to 'stick'. This relies on two primvars :"}
{"id": "c16ead8d3e7c0aa0d63c0501b4895f59c4a96897c8d461196176c50f3e72dd5e", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:20", "text": "that should be present on the deforming geometry. In Maya, use the RenderMan > Primvars > Freeze menu to add them to the selected geometry."}
{"id": "7d3a1c4279d47ed72dc603bfa2784d6890c298e636cb7d45b385508a8e14937e", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:21", "text": "2: WPref - WNref"}
{"id": "3d5e33df03e6b560ba608f8084fa7aad5056cec6e539b7135610e7152bba3652", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:22", "text": "This will allow your projected texture to stick if the object is deforming AND transformed. It relies on"}
{"id": "0b81c331b966c9715c930fd888919b300000aed19a9d4db460147726dbba9e8d", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:24", "text": "primvars. In Maya, use the RenderMan > Primvars > Freeze menu to add them to the selected geometry."}
{"id": "45e1be59069ca2cb3fc3b2811832bcadc8a26ebd2028ea50462c722d6e0ae838", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:25", "text": "Occlusion frontOnly"}
{"id": "fadd0dc90aa1059ec2a7b625a2ab452bfd942027fbc32e317d31fafeba5fc9bf", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:26", "text": "Restricts the projection to the points facing the projection direction."}
{"id": "92af0efbd031de18e2a7fe5616759786eaf458638d4fd746da51651cf5e3f120", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:91", "text": "This setting will update the"}
{"id": "a649c57c3b5ee84a866ba42835bb730023c87296a4b7ad1c61b616ada8548aff", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:138", "text": "resultMask"}
{"id": "2742d7971ff9117f4958061b7fa183dff1b1c98383ab4376f8cf10f5c0b6a9dc", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:93", "text": "output so you may use it to mix between the projection and the underlying surface material."}
{"id": "e07c236563ac37f6fefbe1ff57eef0ab989ae94499edf8475aa4bba46a0bec12", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:30", "text": "Front Falloff"}
{"id": "1fee8eb2b869105170dffad5cb4d9c7f5f532c9b19eef0cb12074e0939239e1f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:31", "text": "Introduces a smooth transition when using frontOnly. Useful to blend transitions between different projections. The default, 0.0, means no falloff."}
{"id": "655f052701fae710159d4c763f42d228aa89791d4e900dbe3adf73d78d98b649", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:35", "text": "Trace Occlusion"}
{"id": "38766ef8cd19fea5dbf3396e03d7babd6483bbdc002fb50cc38607ee0b4125e3", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:36", "text": "Shoots rays to avoid projecting on areas that are occluded by geometry, from the projection's point of view."}
{"id": "f0052b635e5f86f08acce2731bfd7863874174bf605a5856f31c262d002e8e35", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:40", "text": "Trace Max Distance"}
{"id": "687685c84de62e80630dbdca8d846271fc02402161f6fbde607e0d8390f56574", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:41", "text": "When traceOcclusion is on, you can limit the ray length. This number is expressed in scene units, whatever it may be in your authoring package."}
{"id": "4df18aa6ec9b7cf5c8918ae9cf72534e5dab6f422e8dc608179c5092c0df65d5", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:46", "text": "The name of a trace set to restrict ray hits to a specific group of objects. The default is to consider all objects in the scene."}
{"id": "03494b0d1f803522a3497d751eaaf6f987883cd4fe0b0e66baf67a662ae231b2", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:47", "text": "Camera"}
{"id": "52802b9f9da88176db967b51ff75fe806f5ccfba58357460370a20d94729a117", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:48", "text": "Horizontal Resolution"}
{"id": "87fd4fdb37216d5b822abd5975b9f8359b007b848dc86a77dae9ae6df395ab5a", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:49", "text": "The horizontal image resolution. This is used to specify your image's original resolution, prior to txmake-ing."}
{"id": "415b1508e21cb263d660aaf14bdbd2199825b296c19f5188854cb6a4c18b45fb", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:50", "text": "Vertical resolution"}
{"id": "bba507d357f096fd8f59b6ddf3b4f6920157c27ea8bb51acdecc719c9cc65213", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:51", "text": "The vertical image resolution. This is used to specify your image's original resolution, prior to txmake-ing."}
{"id": "8469763ee3691466ffd179a8e970c1f6b1e0153ff705ce6910f60d93453e4b65", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:52", "text": "Horizontal Overscan"}
{"id": "57eaa95c0d4ec9f856feaeb6a1b2d5a1322aeef992482e0353663295f7a8e816", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:53", "text": "Horizontal overscan in pixels"}
{"id": "290922d79d293d401bdb1f39511672842f85b7b6225c34dd8d67d4c94110d397", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:54", "text": "Vertical Overscan"}
{"id": "febbd8f2eaf454a15c4122be74543a83215af25343977ffae70ad0e50989d01a", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:55", "text": "Vertical Overscan in pixels"}
{"id": "c8b9bdc397f3a77fc4f25d49f9cf28d6bdb9d07b0185aec0b5bf370bc2f615c0", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:56", "text": "Camera Type"}
{"id": "c5108ff87cfaed1f944e38c06998867a7e442761c90bb4cfabdb54f924150682", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:57", "text": "Is Orthographic"}
{"id": "602c4a8f8f3d97616b60f34cf1a8f94f94f2dbf69867cfd540ce289288cdc3f8", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:58", "text": "Focal Length"}
{"id": "d0c7b89a359dbf9c2e31b050bbda85ce5800b6d7f839e09a100ac25ac9f1163f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:59", "text": "The focal length of the camera is in millimeters (mm). To convert the Field of View (fov) to the Focal Length, use this"}
{"id": "d00971cda6c6487d049b27ccbcf82215fc4d38325b5f4130e35ea9f221910164", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:60", "text": "Horizontal Aperture"}
{"id": "c30a867da4630913dc2ec63b0678e9637bc78133c9d126a53791e2b156713afa", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:61", "text": "The width of your camera's film back in inches."}
{"id": "7b3d9e64ccc2b0762c8bba3737fc5120358e42f43954f1f501a090e2bf14de6d", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:62", "text": "Vertical Aperture"}
{"id": "85187027091be8506aab2d9dce856eed5ad8adff9e622001edae064ea9106a8e", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:63", "text": "The height of your camera's film back in inches."}
{"id": "e033e1553757dfbebda66b545b92e5130b7506e367ad4a4810874504029dce35", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:64", "text": "Near Clip Plane"}
{"id": "58b201e76903df21602c3e0a182705acf9eb57ce2c5e3f9a6a8c000256740846", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:65", "text": "Positions closer than this distance from the coordinate system will be masked. This number is expressed in scene units, whatever it may be in your authoring package."}
{"id": "9c999c6949dcaa796f3fbb29242cd6be25bed2b0183e4abef8dea8b60985421b", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:69", "text": "Far Clip Plane"}
{"id": "480a2e0538451a9f4c148d2a7ec27afb6cb6cc191490410de1390a8db9913471", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:70", "text": "Positions farther than this distance from the coordinate system will be masked. This number is expressed in scene units, whatever it may be in your authoring package."}
{"id": "376d7261f2c399ca422f6e926da16b4353dd48c0ee250ccebd9cc06962bb224c", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:74", "text": "Film Fit"}
{"id": "6624f336cb41bdd4644ea0f5affa0e8b23464ae232010f60e23156f0edd8f395", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:75", "text": "The way your image is fitted to the film back if they have different aspect ratios. This is mimicking Maya's camera settings."}
{"id": "a4351fd96fba146e19e513acb19eaf3b3666a490fc4f8f196d1ddeabd3936cb7", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:76", "text": "0: Fill"}
{"id": "cea78ac283a283fe1ee899c05276ab0d2d1527fda30b955a3f0dbe624349087c", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:77", "text": "1: Horizontal"}
{"id": "1ce09d6f6ecb9dea0b925cc6d04ec73f24b5ca4adfb32892ca79b033f86d56c5", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:78", "text": "2: Vertical"}
{"id": "28598c3fc46de5145a47d7780ae2ad8b0dc8f066910fe12c81ec20042201d310", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:79", "text": "3: overscan"}
{"id": "e19fee688c50d84e8b0806d9ddfb216ddc514f75eafffe091601072b88af1235", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:95", "text": "Clamp To"}
{"id": "2f1f384eefc37c4e79e75a411d79fc4bcd9005991d68b291f49317f7965b34ce", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:84", "text": "Activates the mask output. You can mask different areas but this is mostly useful with camera projection."}
{"id": "ca7981b46ecf2c1787b6d76d81d9fd7fa0ca95842e2fcc2a452869891a9334d1", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:97", "text": "Off"}
{"id": "3935fe97b094284b4dd8c777ed823e081a63c941bf7005f932c3134db1c7c909", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:86", "text": "The projected texture is everywhere"}
{"id": "66b5ec43c2ca745ac1a978ab470270075a610dd7a999a49395aec10a3fc01868", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:87", "text": "Frustum"}
{"id": "6203b91bc59a521588507a5807c26442be746400fe7dcd41ece6552ea36a4a60", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:88", "text": "The projected texture only appears inside the camera frustum"}
{"id": "e28411a3404d21f9fc1679b4464b3dc497333f6140e580d745d52e2522d65c9f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:89", "text": "Texture"}
{"id": "bbf780c7c5e8e8c80d645d8bc185d13bf965aa0826befc750c8d9a1677980c53", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:90", "text": "The texture is projected in its entirety, irrespective of the camera frustum."}
{"id": "d5794202c621e04f8565ebf57261efe722a98bc85bebc71e08bf7642e6ca3873", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:94", "text": "Planar"}
{"id": "6a90609953a548b80d237db3d394e12e8b334b7d858d3ec8cee4601b38c0832a", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:96", "text": "Clamp the planar projection, assuming the coordinate system is represented as a cube."}
{"id": "c63e4bc94dd1812bcd5c4a3f88e1b9fab896708ab9b084cfec25ae5e8c073cf2", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:98", "text": "The projected texture is everywhere."}
{"id": "c07a3de039fbc0914689549f041eae295d621de7f7f647fd863f6d2f8db2080e", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:99", "text": "XY"}
{"id": "bc031fa3e057dc8ec8c21ae2db61edd75372f850a02602c53ad4263d98cba9b2", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:100", "text": "The projected texture appears on the XY plane of the coordinate system."}
{"id": "3c01374a220b981869ea90ab572b216bf929c389d5dd93b64882bfb4e42ec552", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:101", "text": "XZ"}
{"id": "f1145d457048106109666b4a24c29409f1b2db62ec87ac4492a20a89bcc40df6", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:102", "text": "The projected texture appears on the XZ plane of the coordinate system."}
{"id": "b7198772da96fcef4ced89a98012153597aa661d40e8cb2d38982f57af7b299b", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:103", "text": "YZ"}
{"id": "4c49dbe5b99514213c52819e5127c7ee223b66800ee28e6a23fe23f56914e938", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:104", "text": "The projected texture appears on the YZ plane of the coordinate system."}
{"id": "ade099751d2ea9f3393f0f32d20c6b980dd5d3b0989dea599b966ae0d3cd5a1e", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:105", "text": "XYZ"}
{"id": "fe1be08da82242e22427e37784b71cb480f2238f8c9f9bf1be8f5d0376047249", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:106", "text": "The projected texture appears inside the coordinate system's volume."}
{"id": "6ea3ca903818c96b1452586f8142ba5a7561054e2ed36ecae4f86ce938bf1bef", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:107", "text": "CoordSys Type"}
{"id": "3b17a3ef28fbdd6917207bc7a19d0827f4eb5a108c7c57362bfdeaa5c9988e2e", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:108", "text": "There are 2 different types to match different viewport representations."}
{"id": "0228c6d48ecf92b90092974400dbf3907b57ad1ae7db8e7fd2ae0851e3ba8079", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:109", "text": "Generic"}
{"id": "2dd020a6d95d44471361dd2696b9fd2d83068bf5e2659d760fe9d8211b864d77", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:110", "text": "The coordinate system is a 1 unit wide cube."}
{"id": "51177f803452d5919e1f4cd88fda53b1d9d9c0af0cee1b3098c62cec08dfe42d", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:111", "text": "Maya place3dTexture"}
{"id": "686c156dd20e2aafbe54c728eefed9153588970c2d74cdf79149c6f5b339887f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:112", "text": "the place3dTexture is 2 units wide."}
{"id": "44223178a79aa89af8cedf808edc7c220409ddd0f03a0cf5a4284f6046577701", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:113", "text": "2D Parameters"}
{"id": "1968034b13f84d0c3e441fcc8b5f3ec7b75fcabdbcecb68177445498557d3e33", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:114", "text": "Angle"}
{"id": "b3f120e60d039d1ac78a4368c5da34804d8a65f20d108b93cacfd5de58339968", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:115", "text": "Rotation angle around the origin."}
{"id": "de02ff6a41bb301f28ff4320ea109951b8f00c4bdbd06a50b8b1d6b7d6546538", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:116", "text": "Scale S"}
{"id": "6d29955130e3e9d8ad1d3f2232f63d03cdacb894385163d011e0a681fb06e3c4", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:117", "text": "Frequency of feature in the S direction."}
{"id": "74ed367dd43611959a619b470a288d25878f785a729581a3ec0df16a3ae880b4", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:118", "text": "Scale T"}
{"id": "ddd2e3b3ff5ede4fb11515bb33d91250f4197b8562f175946de4b27879134684", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:119", "text": "Frequency of feature in the T direction."}
{"id": "79182e90c534c862c9a1371a047fc3b73fd5f5b657802cfcfd78324f778ab585", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:120", "text": "Offset S"}
{"id": "420e2a6ad4bb108b4f211a9caa314cd5860b5fc4cdb1ef929b1cde04e994b185", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:121", "text": "Offset from the origin in the S direction."}
{"id": "f25c3396d562c4c180fe177b4acefab8f7fbb413aa193189fa71a156ca5bfd7d", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:122", "text": "Offset T"}
{"id": "eaa14ee7c924af88e3aaa28c365c584e09d0d8198cda7148bf474c4436066723", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:123", "text": "Offset from the origin in the T direction."}
{"id": "e3109eb112b8b5d6dd25efb433f70bf813e165da8c7f3800a0e999d7ee918b11", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:124", "text": "Invert T"}
{"id": "537f65391f4150b2b207f8f7a5f1f95452060e7b424c643ab6fccb9a529c7099", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:125", "text": "Flip the manifold in the T direction."}
{"id": "2cd57109145ab1cb603c7417e2c382756f332d0fc0f9a43b4d461f7d55f5a09f", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:127", "text": "Verbose"}
{"id": "813e30c0dcf1df3130ad73718cc1a8f2fc475a84b578ff3537efe02683ded199", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:128", "text": "Outputs various infos to help you debug your scenes."}
{"id": "b874ed0c9a6ec7882f6f57a395a50e28b899fc8f2436ab486d7c87cae6550fb1", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:129", "text": "Front Only Tolerance"}
{"id": "ccd109942263fb76650d26ebd82409e8f71346ecf37e610d878228994812adaa", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:130", "text": "This parameter is sometimes useful to avoid projecting on surfaces that are close to the grazing angle."}
{"id": "f6a214f7a5fcda0c2cee9660b7fc29f5649e3c68aad48e20e950137c98913a68", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:132", "text": "result"}
{"id": "65843d64082bff47417c75705a19c8f76ad192d79fa54e97f78a5c964b33fceb", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:133", "text": "The 2D manifold."}
{"id": "7e758d48fea0759cce3fe9f56a4494a8bb597ccefaa5e445729806c8a143ebb4", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:134", "text": "resultS"}
{"id": "3e0437d5cc2eac0f36b026681ca43cd3db3d38278341a8c4749b6f6435cba8b7", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:135", "text": "A float representation of the S component of the manifold."}
{"id": "1b45c56fd2090bce37b174f762e471d80f14937615419940f49f5b387705be5a", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:136", "text": "resultT"}
{"id": "239ee435654173264b2f36959a17744f0736f287b609c28833a1a82c1b3f2764", "item_id": "3ab2b8760a:137", "text": "A float representation of the T component of the manifold."}
